    "abl.eyebrow":"In 3 steps","abl.title":"How working together works","abl.s1t":"Report the accident","abl.s1d":"Briefly describe your traffic accident – via WhatsApp, e-mail or phone. Reply usually within 24 hours.","abl.s2t":"Send documents","abl.s2d":"You send us any documents and photos. We assess your claims and, if needed, instruct an independent expert.","abl.s3t":"We take over","abl.s3d":"We handle the full settlement with the other party's liability insurer and enforce your claims – you don't have to argue with the insurer.",
    "faq.eyebrow":"Frequently asked questions","faq.title":"Answers after a traffic accident","faq.q1":"What does instructing you cost me?","faq.a1":"In a no-fault traffic accident, the other party's liability insurer regularly covers the necessary legal fees. No legal expenses insurance is required for this.","faq.q2":"Do I need legal expenses insurance?","faq.a2":"No. In a no-fault accident the other party's insurer usually covers the costs. If you are at fault, legal expenses insurance helps – we clarify this with you in advance.","faq.q3":"May I choose my own expert?","faq.a3":"Yes. In a no-fault accident you have the right to your own independent expert – not the one from the other party's insurer.","faq.q4":"How quickly will I get a response?","faq.a4":"Usually within 24 hours. The fastest way to reach us is via WhatsApp.","faq.q5":"Do you also represent nationwide?","faq.a5":"Yes. The process is digital, so we can represent you throughout Germany."
